ecent discovery of rings orbiting small outer Solar System bodies\n(Centaurs), and the possible rings around extrasolar planets. In section 6, we\nconclude and try to identify critical observations and theoretical advances\nneeded to better understand the origin of rings and their significance in the\nglobal evolution of planets.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 28 Mar 2017 18:40:49 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-10-17"}
