false positives in our candidates and the main\nbelt actually contains many low level active asteroids undetected by current\nsurveys. Case C) would imply that the main belt is not a field of bare rocks\nbut a graveyard of extinct comets, changing our current paradigm of the main\nbelt. So it is of the outmost importance to verify observationally our\ncandidates, and determine which of these scenarios is valid.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 29 Mar 2017 05:40:04 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-03-30"}
